  "prompt": "Does the files sent through share it have less resolution?",
  "response": "The resolution of files sent through Shareit or any other file-sharing application should remain the same as the original file, provided that the transfer is completed successfully and the file is not corrupted during the process. Shareit does not compress or alter the resolution of image, video, or any other type of file during the transfer. However, if the transfer is interrupted or if there is an issue with the internet connection, it could potentially result in a corrupted file, which may appear to have a lower resolution or quality.",
